        "text": "The men of every city; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " comprehensively taken, so as to include women and children. If this seem harsh and bloody, either it may be ascribed to military fury; or rather, it may be justified; partly, from that high guilt brought upon the whole tribe, in which it is no wonder if their infants suffered, which was not unusual in such cases, as ",
        "children": []
